The paper discusses recent advances in human action recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses machine learning techniques and deep learning architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses applications of human action recognition in video retrieval and human-machine interaction, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) categories, respectively.
